struct rdma_resources {
    // ... existing members
    struct doca_buf *local_bufs[NUM_TRANSFERS];
    struct doca_buf *remote_bufs[NUM_TRANSFERS];
    int curr_buf_idx;
};

get bufs from inventory in initialization function and lookthem up later through the array
Create big array to fit all buffers. I had an issue that if i didnt decrease the ref count of the buffers i couldnt reuse them so i would have to get again a new buf each 
time and nothing would change. So now i have an array of 1000 buffers. Not oprimal but for now it will suffice
